
[1]goodman

   GOOD'MAN, n. A familiar appellation of civility; sometimes used
   ironically.

   With you, goodman boy, if you please.

   1. A rustic term of compliment; as old goodman Dobson.

   2. A familiar appellation of a husband; also,the master of a family.
   Prov.7. Matt.24.
